          "subtype": "message",
          "text": "Now I have all the information I need. The bug is clear: the `iwl_dev_info_table` array in `drivers/net/wireless/intel/iwlwifi/pcie/drv.c` is missing three entries for device 0x2526 (Intel Wireless-AC 9260) with subdevice IDs 0x0401, 0x4018, and 0x401C.\n\nThese missing entries cause the firmware to not be loaded correctly because:\n1. The PCI device ID table (`iwl_hw_card_ids`) has a catch-all entry with `PCI_ANY_ID` for subdevice\n2. The device info table (`iwl_dev_info_table`) is searched for more specific matches during probe\n3. If specific subdevice IDs are not in the table, they fall through to the generic catch-all config instead of getting the correct 9260-specific firmware configuration\n\nLet me create the fault localization result:",
