          "arguments": {
            "content": "{\n  \"buggy_files\": [\n    \"drivers/net/wireless/intel/iwlwifi/pcie/drv.c\"\n  ],\n  \"buggy_functions\": [\n    \"iwl_dev_info_table\"\n  ],\n  \"confidence\": 0.95,\n  \"reasoning\": \"The iwl_dev_info_table (device info table) in drivers/net/wireless/intel/iwlwifi/pcie/drv.c is missing three IWL_DEV_INFO entries for device 0x2526 (Intel Wireless-AC 9260) with subdevice IDs 0x0401, 0x4018, and 0x401C. The table currently has entries for subdevice IDs 0x0010, 0x0014, 0x0018, 0x001C, 0x6010, 0x6014, 0x8010, 0x8014, 0xA014, 0xE010, 0xE014 (iwl9260 variants), and 0x0030, 0x0038, 0x003C, 0x4030 (iwl9560 variants), but lacks the three mentioned subdevice entries. When a device with these subdevice IDs is enumerated, the iwl_pci_probe function searches this table for device/subdevice-specific configuration. Without matching entries, the device falls through to the catch-all PCI_ANY_ID entry which uses a generic configuration instead of the proper iwl9260_2ac_160_cfg configuration, causing firmware loading failures. The fix requires adding three new IWL_DEV_INFO macro invocations to the iwl_dev_info_table for subdevice IDs 0x0401, 0x4018, and 0x401C with the iwl9260_2ac_160_cfg configuration and iwl9260_160_name name string, similar to the existing 0x001x entries.\"\n}\n",
